/young-adults-face-major-cannabis-risk-knowledge-gaps</link><description>大麻使用者是否充分了解大麻风险意识？这是最近发表在《大麻研究杂志》上的一项研究希望解决的问题 |大麻科学&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/young-adults-face-major-cannabis-risk-knowledge-gaps.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 01:09:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/young-adults-face-major-cannabis-risk-knowledge-gaps</guid></item><item><title>新研究表明人类可能具有隐藏的再生能力</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/humans-may-have-hidden-regenerative-powers-new-study-suggests</link><description>研究人员已经成功地再生了骨骼和结缔组织，尽管新组织尚未完美形成。结果表明肢体再生向前迈出了关键一步。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/humans-may-have-hidden-regenerative-powers-new-study-suggests.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 00:54:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/humans-may-have-hidden-regenerative-powers-new-study-suggests</guid></item><item><title>监管衍生的 TGF-β 信号传导控制肿瘤浸润旁观者 CD8+ T 细胞的分化和维持</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/regulatory-derived-tgf-%ce%b2-signaling-governs-the-differentiation-and-maintenance-of-tumor-infiltrating-bystander-cd8-t-cells</link><description>林等人。揭示肿瘤浸润旁观者 CD8+ T 细胞是异质的，并经历 TCM 到 TEM 到 TRM 的分化轨迹，该轨迹由 Treg 衍生的 TGF-β 信号传导通过抑制 KLF2 驱动。这种机制维持了旁观者 CD8+ T 细胞的异质性和在肿瘤中的积累，并为癌症免疫治疗提供了一种可靶向的机制。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/regulatory-derived-tgf-ceb2-signaling-governs-the-differentiation-and-maintenance-of-tumor-infiltrating-bystander-cd8-t-cells.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 00:39:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/regulatory-derived-tgf-%ce%b2-signaling-governs-the-differentiation-and-maintenance-of-tumor-infiltrating-bystander-cd8-t-cells</guid></item><item><title>科学家改变了生命形式的基本密码。它不应该幸存下来——但它确实幸存了</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/scientists-changed-a-lifeforms-fundamental-code-it-shouldnt-have-survived-but-it-did</link><description>生命——至少据我们所知——需要 20 种氨基酸，将它们结合成构建活组织的蛋白质。生命实际上是如何达到至少20岁的&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/scientists-changed-a-lifeforms-fundamental-code-it-shouldnt-have-survived-but-it-did.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 00:24:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/scientists-changed-a-lifeforms-fundamental-code-it-shouldnt-have-survived-but-it-did</guid></item><item><title>宇宙就像生命形式一样演化</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-universe-evolves-like-a-life-form</link><description>如果物理定律不是固定的，而是不断发展的怎么办？&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-universe-evolves-like-a-life-form.webp" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 00:09:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-universe-evolves-like-a-life-form</guid></item><item><title>分析显示，远程医疗的使用在没有增加医疗就诊或支出的情况下增长</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/telemedicine-use-grew-without-boosting-medical-visits-or-spending-analysis-shows</link><description>加州大学洛杉矶分校领导的新研究发现，远程医疗的使用并没有显着增加所有付款人类型的就诊次数和医疗支出。研究结果， &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/telemedicine-use-grew-without-boosting-medical-visits-or-spending-analysis-shows.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 11 May 2026 23:54:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/telemedicine-use-grew-without-boosting-medical-visits-or-spending-analysis-shows</guid></item><item><title>新“技巧”修复了中性原子量子计算机的主要缺陷——让我们更接近超级强大的系统</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/new-trick-fixes-major-flaw-in-neutral-atom-quantum-computers-inching-us-closer-to-a-superpowerful-system</link><description>一种新的“基于几何”的量子交换门使中性原子计算机对激光噪声的敏感度大大降低，使大规模、稳定的量子处理器离现实又近了一步。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/new-trick-fixes-major-flaw-in-neutral-atom-quantum-computers-inching-us-closer-to-a-superpowerful-system2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubD